lenders.name: Jeremy
lenders.loan_because: As an Englishman I am rich, not in the sense that I have a lot of money, but I am really rich in that I live in a democratic country where I can speak freely and have my own opinions. As a retired teacher of 67 I am privileged in that I have an occupational pension (which I paid into during my years teaching) and a state pension since I was 65 (which I have contributed through the taxes I have paid). I discovered Kiva because the son of an old friend gave me a $25 Kiva gift card. Since that first loan I am now on my fifteenth loan. I am so happy to loan this way because I can read about the potential borrowers and can make my own choice where and to whom I loan. Kiva is a true system of "A hand up, not a hand out". It is admirable that the vast majority of borrowers pay back on time or early. These people clearly see it as their responsibility to do so and thus honour the work of Kiva. It is so easy to feel that one single human can do little to solve the multitude of human problems and catastrophies, but through Kiva I am proud to feel that I can make a little, but valuable change in some people's lives. By merely being born British I grew up where, although we have many poor and unemployed, the conditions are so much better and more peaceful than in so many parts of the world today. I am a human being and ALL other humans are my sisters and brothers. It has been my good fortune to travel to many countries where humble and poor people have shown me such kindness and generosity. It is my experience that those who have least are usually the most generous! I embrace all humans. There should ONLY be love and affection instead of fear and hatred.
lenders.occupational_info: I retired from teaching aged 53 because I have tinnitus and I am going deaf. Before and after my 26 years as a teacher I have worked: washing up in a London restaurant, in New Zealand I taught and then worked as a welder's mate and then as a storeman in a shoe factory. Back in Britain I worked as a social worker with old people, as a storeman at a gas depot, giving art evening classes and as a webmaster (web site designer) for two companies. I married aged 58 to a lady I had worked with years before. We sing in classical concerts. I love mountains, music, cooking, baking bread and cakes, I read avidly. I very happily became a step father to three and a step grandfather to two. Life is a gift, use it well, live it to the full and share the good times and pass on to the young your own love of life.
